  The errors from our model are normally distributed.</p> <br> <p class=3D"=
body-text"><span class=3D"bold">When Assumptions Fail?</span> <br>
  What should we do if the assumptions for our regression model aren't met?=
 Don't
  fret, it's not the end of the world! First, double-check that the assumpt=
ions even
  matter in the first place: if the predictions made from our model general=
ize well
  to unseen data, and our task is to create a model that generalizes well, =
then we're
  probably fine. If not, figure out which assumption is being violated, and=
